{
  "texts": [
    "WebT-ext2 data was sourced from outbound Reddit links with an upvote of 3 or more as a proxy for quality.",
    "Reddit has been noted to contain discourse with significant sexist [27], racist [49], and hateful political content [48].",
    "whilst Wikipedia has been shown to have a problem representing under-served groups [30].GPT-3.5 was released in March 2022, and builds upon its predecessor, GPT3.",
    "Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) was used as part of the training process.",
    "The RLHF process involves training the model using feedback from human annotators who review the outputs generated by the model and provide ratings or corrections."
  ]
}